# How has the Wagner group been involved in the Russia-Ukraine conflict?

## Summary
The Wagner Group, a mercenary organization headed by Russian oligarch Yevgeny Prigozhin, has been a key player in the Russia-Ukraine conflict. It has done much of the fighting in the small eastern town of Soledar and has expanded its global footprint since its creation in 2014, with accusations of war crimes in Africa, Syria and Ukraine <font color=#FF3399>[1, 2]</font>. It is estimated that there are around 50,000 Wagner Group fighters currently deployed to Ukraine <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font>, and they have become a rival power center to the Russian military and other Russian ministries <font color=#FF3399>[4]</font>. Yevgeny Prigozhin has complained that the Russian Ministry of Defense has not provided his group with enough equipment, authority and autonomy to carry out operations in Ukraine <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font>. Last week, the US imposed additional sanctions against Wagner and its support network, and a defector from the group has spoken out, fearing for his life after refusing to renew his service with Wagner <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font>.

